io.vertx.ext.web.api.contract.openapi3

Interface OpenAPI3RouterFactory

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DesignDrivenRouterFactory<io.swagger.oas.models.OpenAPI>

    public interface OpenAPI3RouterFactory
extends DesignDrivenRouterFactory<io.swagger.oas.models.OpenAPI>
    Interface for OpenAPI3RouterFactory.
    To add an handler, use addHandlerByOperationId(String, Handler), in this class is better than generic DesignDrivenRouterFactory.addHandler(HttpMethod, String, Handler)
    If you want to use DesignDrivenRouterFactory.addHandler(HttpMethod, String, Handler) remember that you have to pass path as declared in openapi specification Usage example: 
     
 OpenAPI3RouterFactory.createRouterFactoryFromFile(vertx, "src/resources/spec.yaml", asyncResult -> {
  if (!asyncResult.succeeded()) {
     // IO failure or spec invalid
  } else {
     OpenAPI3RouterFactory routerFactory = asyncResult.result();
     routerFactory.addHandlerByOperationId("operation_id", routingContext -> {
        // Do something
     }, routingContext -> {
        // Do something with failure handler
     });
     Router router = routerFactory.getRouter();
  }
 });
    Author:
    Francesco Guardiani @slinkydeveloper
